svm_eval<-function(model, data, truth) {
  #get the predicted value for all the set
  pred <- predict(model, data)
  #Confusion Matrix
  print(table(pred, truth,
              dnn=c("Predicted", "Actual")))
  #Accuracy = sum of diagonal elements/no. of observation
  cat("Accuracy:", sum(diag(table(pred, truth)))/nrow(data))
}

# split data into training and test sets
set.seed(800)
index <- 1:nrow(df)
test_set_index <- sample(index, trunc(length(index)/3))
test_set <- df[test_set_index,]
training_set <- df[-test_set_index,]
# train CART
# create task
cart_task <- makeClassifTask(id = "dt", data = training_set,
                             target = "Class")
# create learner
cart_lrn <- makeLearner("classif.rpart", minsplit=1, minbucket=1, cp=0.001,
                        xval=10,
                        parms=list(split="gini"))
# define training resampling strategy
rdesc <- makeResampleDesc(method = "CV", iters=10)
# tune cp and set the other parameters to constant
num_ps <- makeParamSet(
  makeNumericParam("cp", lower = -5, upper = 5, trafo =
                     function(x) 10^x)
  
  
)
ctrl <- makeTuneControlRandom(maxit = 200L)
res <- tuneParams(cart_lrn, task = cart_task,
                  resampling = rdesc,
                  par.set = num_ps,
                  control = ctrl,
                  measures = list(acc, mmce),
                  show.info = FALSE)
res
## Tune result:
## Op. pars: cp=0.0469
## acc.test.mean=0.7549451,mmce.test.mean=0.2450549
# update hyperparameter
cart_lrn <- setHyperPars(cart_lrn, par.vals = res$x)
cart_lrn
## Learner classif.rpart from package rpart
## Type: classif
## Name: Decision Tree; Short name: rpart
## Class: classif.rpart
## Properties: twoclass,multiclass,missings,numerics,factors,ordered,prob,weights,featimp
## Predict-Type: response
## Hyperparameters: xval=10,minsplit=1,minbucket=1,cp=0.0469,parms=split=gini
# train C50
# create task
c50_task <- makeClassifTask(id = "dt", data = training_set,
                            target = "Class")
# create learner
c50_lrn <- makeLearner("classif.C50", CF=0.1, minCases=2)
# define training resampling strategy
rdesc <- makeResampleDesc(method = "CV", iters=10)
# tune CF
num_ps <- makeParamSet(
  makeNumericParam("CF", lower = -5, upper = 0, trafo =
                     function(x) 10^x)
)
ctrl <- makeTuneControlRandom(maxit = 200L)
res <- tuneParams(c50_lrn, task = c50_task,
                  resampling = rdesc,
                  par.set = num_ps,
                  control = ctrl,
                  measures = list(acc, mmce),
                  show.info = FALSE)
res
## Tune result:
## Op. pars: CF=0.808
## acc.test.mean=0.7186813,mmce.test.mean=0.2813187
# update hyperparameter
c50_lrn <- setHyperPars(c50_lrn, par.vals = res$x)
c50_lrn

# create benchmark tasks
bmr_task <- makeClassifTask(id = "dt-benchmark", data = df,
                            target = "Class")
# create learners for the optimized cart and c50 learners and randomForest
lrns = list(cart_lrn,
            c50_lrn,
            makeLearner("classif.randomForest"))
# define resampling strategy
rdesc <- makeResampleDesc(method = "CV", iters=10)

# conduct the benchmark
bmr = benchmark(lrns, bmr_task, rdesc, measures=list(acc, mmce, ber))
